title: Women's Cycling 101 Clinic
description: Women\\\'s Cycling 101 Clinic:  3 days - which will include a day of instruction and skills clinics, followed by 2 days of (optional) racing with the Frozen Flatlands Omnium Stage Race (TT, Road Race, and Circuit Race).  This clinic is aimed at beginning racers and recreational riders of all ages.  Supportive, ability-based clinic that focuses on both classroom and on-the-road learning.
course:
Day 1:  Course in/around Coeur D Alene Idaho for skills work
Day 2:  AM Time Trial for those participating in the Frozen Flatlands Omnium Stage Race
        PM Road Race for those participating in the Frozen Flatlands Omnium Stage Race
Day 3:  Circuit Race for those participating in the Frozen Flatlands Omnium Stage Race
registration:
Register by completing the online PDF flyer at www.teamriverstone.com and mail to 
Jenni Gaertner
214 N Bruce Dr
Coeur D Alene, ID  83814
By March 28, 2009
Or, stop by Vertical Earth (308 Coeur D Alene Ave, Coeur D Alene, ID) to pick up a flyer and drop off registration.
Day of registration will have an additional fee of $10.  Please pre-register, to best assist in planning for instructor:rider ratios.
Registration for the Forzen Flatlands Omnium Stage Race is SEPARATE, and can be completed online at www.baddlands.org
